<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Aldur:
[B]Luclin has changed alot for ae groups.

Mobs in general are higher and hence resist much more making 2 enchanters in luclin AE groups a definite bonus.  Combine that with the fact that the puller has run speed 3, means that there is much less damage to be healed so swopping a healer out for an enchanter is a good move.

Its not completely fool proof (still had one wipe out - only one I had in 15 hours of ae though) where one of the chanters fizzled stun twice, I was low on mana, I fizzled group heal, then the fizzle script tried to cast it again and I didn't have the mana.  It took me a second to notice what was going on and by that time one of the chanters had gone done, and with 30 odd mid 50 critters sitting in camp, things got dicey quickly :>

I typically have

Remedy
Divine Light
Unspoken word
Upheaval
CE
Aegolism (I am too lazy to mem stun command - it really doesn't help when you have a pull of 41.)
Word of Vigor
Da [/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
