<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShelseaDruid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am currently a 55 Cleric and have only done 3 AE groups.  They seem to be quite popular though.  What spells should be memmed and what group setup is suggested.<P>/hugs<BR>Torriana Shaddowfists<BR>55 Cleric<BR>Brell Serilis</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Depends on if you play a strict healing role, or nuking healing role.  I tend to do both.<P>I keep Upheaval, Unspoken Word, Word of Restoration, CE, DL, and an AE stun.<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>60th High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Succoring Winds<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">varthdadur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've been in about 5 AE groups now, give or take a few.  The group makeup is always the same:<P>BARD<BR>CLERIC<BR>ENCHANTER<BR>ENCHANTER<BR>WIZARD<BR>WIZARD<P>For this group I forget CH and memorize upheaval--if I have a lot of mana I cast this once for 725 AE damage, costs a lot of mana (600+?) but its fun to see all those spell damage messages spam your screen!  I have the spell stun command so I keep that memorized even though it only has a max of 4 targets.  I keep Remedy and Divine light for fast heals.  Celestial Elixir (you can use Cel healing) is used on the bard right before he pulls.  Also, I usually have heroic bond for a quick group heal but I rarely have found a use for it.  I'm looking for a good replacement for this slot.  I keep divine aura but don't have much of a use for it (if it gets that bad usually you are toast either way).<P>As far as buffs I give everyone HB, AC buff everyone using my Donal's gloves except I put Bulwark on the puller, and give everyone Marzin.<P>-Varth L59 Templar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Depends on if you play a strict healing role, or nuking healing role.  I tend to do both.<P>I keep Upheaval, Unspoken Word, Word of Restoration, CE, DL, and an AE stun.<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>60th High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Succoring Winds<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I typically load<P>WoV or WoR<BR>Remedy<BR>CE<BR>Upheavel<BR>Stun Command (new SoL 39 AE stun works too, I just prefer the faster cast of SC)<BR>DA (never changes)<BR>DL<BR>DB<P>And our AE groups are usually <BR>Puller<BR>Chanter<BR>Cleric<BR>Wizard<BR>Wizard<BR>Wizard<P>I spam Remedy when the puller is out getting mobs until I start to cast. That usually brings the house down on me for a minute and with my AC I can take a few hits (better than the chanter getting it). If it gets too hot that's when you pull out SC (which you should be able to resist) and pull back. By the time SC wears off the chanter will be in full AE stun mode and the wizards will be AEing like mad. I usually CE the puller around this time and/or follow up with a DL. Then I Remedy/DL/CE as needed. That's usually it. Occasionally you'll get a chance to toss an Upheavel and burn off some mana but be sure it's safe to do so before you cast. One tiny screwup and you'll burn all your mana on heals.<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>High Priest of Prexus<BR><A HREF="http://www.cohort.cc" TARGET=_blank>Cohort Chalybeius</A><BR>Cazic Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Luclin has changed alot for ae groups.<P>Mobs in general are higher and hence resist much more making 2 enchanters in luclin AE groups a definite bonus.  Combine that with the fact that the puller has run speed 3, means that there is much less damage to be healed so swopping a healer out for an enchanter is a good move.<P>Its not completely fool proof (still had one wipe out - only one I had in 15 hours of ae though) where one of the chanters fizzled stun twice, I was low on mana, I fizzled group heal, then the fizzle script tried to cast it again and I didn't have the mana.  It took me a second to notice what was going on and by that time one of the chanters had gone done, and with 30 odd mid 50 critters sitting in camp, things got dicey quickly :><P>I typically have<P>Remedy<BR>Divine Light<BR>Unspoken word<BR>Upheaval<BR>CE<BR>Aegolism (I am too lazy to mem stun command - it really doesn't help when you have a pull of 41.)<BR>Word of Vigor<BR>Da </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Klairen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">With this group...<P>Wizard<BR>Wizard<BR>Wizard<BR>Enchanter<BR>Cleric<BR>Rogue<P>...we can easily keep a wing clear in HS. Two divines will let me make one huge pull every 7ish minutes. And Improved ITU helps me get into a good position to pull from. It's almost too easy.<P>I use these spells...<P>Divine A<BR>Divine B<BR>Elixir<BR>Remedy<BR>WoR(57)<BR>Improved ITU<BR>Stun Command<BR>Upheaval<P>For non-undead stuff, I'd substitute Unspoken Word in place of Improved ITU.<P>In most dungeons, just gather as many mobs as you dare, hit a Divine, gather some more, then run back to the group. In HS, it's a good idea to bounce all the harm touches, so you'll need to divine right before you pull.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4758" TARGET=_blank>Klair</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My ae spell lineup is: CE, Remedy, CH, WoR, DA, DB, Upheaval, Stun Command.  If I'm not puller (clerics make great pullers in HS with DB/DA to eat the HT's), I drop DB for Unspoken Word.  Remedy's range makes it nice for healing the puller on inc if they're taking too much damage.  Our ae groups vary a lot, and with competent players just about any class combination works as long as two in the group can ae.  I've even done successful ae groups without enchanters before, tho enchanters really make it easy.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Iudar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Who's pulling?  If it's you, have all your Divine Auras up, a fast casting heal, a better heal, and if you have room, Upheaval (why not?  might as well nuke too, not much healing needed after the pull).  If someone else is pulling, lose some of the Divines, load a stun or two just in case, and perhaps a root.<P>Things to remember.  AoE groups are virtually always Pure Caster only, save for the Cleric and/or Bard.<P>Self buffed, I have about 1200hp, not very much.<P><B>FAST</B> Heals are critical.  You'll probably never need Complete Heal in an AoE group, what you need is to be able to pop those heals off on the chanters quickly when a few of the mobs resist the stun.  Unless pulling, the AoE damage casters will rarely take any hits, but the chanters will take some lumps while they get them stun locked, and looking stupid.<P><BR>Once the pull is completed, and the heals done, cut loose on your damage yourselves, have a little fun.<P>Happy Training !</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
